-- Rabigh Refining Works to Resume Power Supply After Outage Affects Plants
-- B y   S h a j i   M a t h e w
-- 2010-10-24T05:46:56Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-24/rabigh-refining-works-to-resume-power-supply-after-outage-affects-plants.html
Rabigh Refining and Petrochemicals
Co., a joint venture between state-owned Saudi Aramco and
Sumitomo Chemical Co. of Japan, said its operations were
affected by an interruption of power supply yesterday.  “Efforts are currently in progress to resume power
supplies and restore units operations to its normal status,”
the company said in a statement to the Saudi bourse today.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Shaji Mathew at 
 shajimathew@bloomberg.net  